caption: The food is always amazing every time I get it here and the staff are so nice as well!!
Super good tasting. Had the street tacos, a veggie pita, and a piece of pie. Some of the best vegan restaurant food I've had. Well worth the price
cruelty free!!
The food is absolutely amazing! All vegan and soooo delicious! I highly recommend

Boise people- you are so lucky to have this healthy gem. My hubby said he would move here just to eat here. Everything is so fresh with terrific flavors.  We ordered the Gyro that tasted just like the ones I used to eat at non- vegan Greek restaurants, but better. The cup of cream of coconut tomato basil soup was sublime. And the Breakfast burrito- amazing flavors wrapped in yumminess. Come hungry. Save room for the pie! Maybe tomorrow.... We will definitely plan our next trip around mealtimes here. Did I tell you about the great customer service? We liked the music and art, as well. Ending our vacation on a High Note. THANK YOU FOR A 5 STAR EXPERIENCE.

I hardly ever leave reviews, but just had High Note since they switched to all vegan (I know, I realize now I waited wayyy too long!) I got the Habanero Hominy Quesadilla and it is SO good! SO good that I’m eating leftovers right now and am still obsessed. Good spiciness, but not over powering. The sauces compliment perfectly too! Definitely adding High Note to my regular take-out rotation!
Stopped here on our way through and we weren't disappointed! Burrito was delicious as was tht Gyro!

It's hard to find all vegan restaurants, and this one does not disappoint. I just ate here for the first time today and it was amazing. My stomach is very happy. The homemade hummus knocked my socks off and the seitan tasted like jerky! Even if you're not vegan, you will enjoy this place. I'll be supporting this business often.
BEST FOOD IN TOWN!! The only vegan place I’ve found and have craved days after!!
Absolute best food in town

First off, the food here is great and I think the menu offerings are the best vegan options in Boise. Everything I've tried on the menu is exceptional. The service here is friendly as well.  The reason for 3 stars is due to the difficulty of ordering over the phone. On one occasion I was referencing the menu found on their website, and the employee had no idea what some of the menu items were. They then admitted they hadn't looked at the updated menu, and the whole process took over ten minutes to place a simple order.  On another occasion, I placed an order for a breakfast burrito which comes with 7 toppings, and once I got all the way back home, my burrito only had 5 of the 7 I asked for (there was no cheese, and no cilantro cream sauce). Considering the price for just a burrito is $12, I was very disappointed and didn't have the time to go all the way back to ask for a corrected order.  The orders here take a while to be made, which is fine, but if I can't call ahead on the phone and trust my order will be right, it will make me think twice about placing a dinner/lunch order here.

Omg this place is incredible!!! We just had some for lunch had the mini tacos and we were blown away!!! All the ingredients complemented each other so well!! Also tried the vegan tomato soup with gluten free bread grilled cheese and OMG everything was incredibly delicious!!!! And EVERYTHING is vegan at this restaurant!!! We can't wait to go again!!! I had the raspberry mint drink it was so refreshing slightly sweet with that tartness from raspberries ughhhh everything was incredible!!!!!! Great job guys!!!! This is our NEW favorite vegan spot !!!!! 💣💣💣
Bit spendy but fantastic culture and inclusiveness. A recommend for a date

Best food EVER! I can't believe how many flavors they create and combine for decadent sandwiches that I would never think to make at home. The pesto mushroom is a real favorite. Their horseradish cream sauce is ridiculously good... and the Caesar salad... WOW! What a wonderful place to enjoy - or rather, take food out from and enjoy at home. The inside looks lovely, too, and someday when the pandemic is contained, eating inside will be a delight, too!

I love every dish I've tried at High Note, and I think I've had everything on the menu! The soup varies from day to day, so I've probably missed a few, and I can say that just when I think there can be no soup better than the African Squash, High Note's amazing chef wowed me with the cream of spinach. I alternate between three favorite meals: Rosemary Seitan and Pesto Mushroom sandwiches and the breakfast burrito, and either the soup of the day or caesar salad. I'd eat here every  day if my pocket book could afford it. I was skimming the reviews and noted most people love High Note as much as I do. I want to comment on a couple of poor reviews b/c they should not deter someone from trying the best restaurant in Boise. There was a complaint/dig about them going to cash & check only. I wish that person would have asked about the why behind that decision - it speaks volumes about the integrity of the owner. The money saved each month in not paying for the credit card machine (that's a BIG hunk of money it turns out) is going to employees in extra salary b/c they're working through a pandemic. It's a brilliant decision to support people working in an industry that's really hard hit by covid, and I don't even consider it an inconvenience (it's old school charming, actually! my grandma and grandpa never even had a credit card, and they were the cutest cash-paying couple ever). There was also criticism from someone who waited a while for their food. I'm sure that was frustrating; however, I am also certain that experience was an outlier. I have probably gotten take out at least 25 times since High Note reopened after their temporary closure, and I've never waited more than a couple of minutes for my food - and I'm happy to wait so that my yummy sandwich is piping hot! High Note is amazing - I can't say enough good things!
Great vegan food!! I was pleasantly surprised to find an all vegan food restaurant in Boise. Absolutely superb quality, too! 10/10 recommend!
Favorite spot for breakfast, lunch, and dinner...honestly you can't go wrong with anything on the menu. Best food in Boise :)
I LOVE this place! All their food is delicious. I come here weekly and they never disappoint.
Breakfast burrito is reallyyyy good! Super filling too. My wife loved the breakfast sandwich also. And the breakfast potatoes are quite good too!

Looks like a great place but cash only when most places are leaning to card only is not a smart idea.  This will cause a loss of new customers leaving you behind in the times.   Good luck staying afloat.

This place is incredible.  What amazing food. Brought a very strict only meat eater to this place for his first vegan meal. He said he absolutely loved it, had no idea it was vegan. Before this he was afraid of it!  Super friendly staff as well.  @wanderlustmoonduo

I rarely leave reviews on Google but... I have been to vegan restaurants in Colorado and Washington, and this place is one of the best. We got tacos, quesadillas, and the gyro sandwich. Everything was impeccable.
The Vegan Breakfast Burrito is the best burrito you can get in Boise. I’m not vegan but that burrito SLAPS

Wanted to support a local vegan restaurant while in town, & found this place on Happy Cow. We ordered takeout & were told they would put our order outside on the patio table for us to pick up. We called when we arrived at the restaurant 20 minutes later & were again told they would put our order outside on the patio table when it was ready. After waiting another 20 minutes (40 minutes total) we called a third time & were told our order had been ready for a while & that they had put it inside the door. No apologies for their miscommunication, & the server tried to blame it on another employee even though I'm pretty sure it was the same person on the phone all three times. Our food was fine, but cold. Oh, also the forks they gave us were broken? Not a big deal but definitely icing on the cake.
The Best.
Delicious vegan food!
Such yummy food and I really like the way they are respecting social distancing!

I'm so glad that we found this restaurant. We had a work meeting and had them make our lunch. Everyone ordered something different and everyone loved what they got. We will definitely be using High Note Cafe for future catering.
Wonderful cafe! Kind and friendly owners! The food is delicious and the apple crumb cake is incredible!

I have been a fan of High Note Cafe for more than a year.  The owner, management and the employees care deeply about their customers and our community. When the city announced that they were going to shut down businesses in March, I was there on their last open night. It was a heartfelt goodbye in uncertain times but the owner said to me, ' This is not goodbye, we will be back, when it is safe for customers and our team.'   Anyone can be a small business owner but not everyone can succeed. High Note Cafe has survived and will continue to thrive due their passion for doing things right. I am encouraged and excited about them reopening soon as they bring a tremendous joy and smiles to countless Boise residents near and far. Whether it is a two hand delicious breakfast burrito, homemade bread, Jalapeno hominy, or Tuesday tacos, I and many more will continue to support High Note Cafe in the coming weeks and longer because they make a difference in our community.

Good food, but they don’t answer they’re phone to place orders for pickup and they’re “voicemail inbox” is full.. If they’re closed, they haven’t reported it to Google yet.  The owner clearly doesn’t know how to run a business.  Just go to the Boise Co-Op.
Had the impossible burger and it was so good
Amazing food! All plant based and so so so tasty. Amazing service. Definitely coming back!
Everything was great. Maybe too much grease and salt. Not fault of the restaurant. This is the way the food is prepared.
Hands down best karaoke place in town. Wednesday nights beginning at 7pm it’s church here. A nonbeliever will breathe new life here. Robin will treat you to amazing drinks and some hell of treats.
Vegan, pricey, tasty
Vegan! Entertainment! Amazing juice.

How do I start? Ummm, WOW! What a pleasant surprise this place was. I had a girlfriend in town from up north who has recently switched to all vegan cuisine. Needless to say I was hoping we could find a restaurant that could cater to her dietary needs. It was 8:30 on a Friday night so we were really pushing the limits of availability here. A quick Google search offered High Note. We were in luck as they closed in about an hour. We headed over in hopes of finding accommodating sustenance. So not only was it a cute, little "hole-in-the-wall" type place, but we were happy to find artwork from local artists lining their red walls. The waitress was attentive and friendly. Now...the food. I have been to other vegan restaurants and have left less than satisfied as far as the food was concerned regarding taste and portion, but let me tell you, this place left neither lacking. The portions were extremely gracious (in accordance with menu pricing) and the taste rivaled even most non vegan restaurants. I only wish I could have taken pictures to share. I HIGHLY recommend this local treasure to anyone, vegan or not. The food is beyond the labels and if you don't try them it is only to your disservice. Well done High Note, we definitely left on one. ;)

Been trying to pair down my meat and fat  intake... Hit up the High Note a couple times recently... Very nice selection of vegetarian/vegan sandwiches, appetizers and quesadillas. My only real complaint is things seem to be underseasoned, but a dash of salt really brought out the flavors and freshness.

I came to visit Boise and was pleased to find this Vegan restaurant. I had the butternut squash soup and a sandwich. Both were amazing and delicious!!! I can not stop thinking about that soup, and just had to leave a review. The staff was very friendly and the atmosphere was great!
Best tomato soup and live music!
Delicious vegan food and a great staff!
I’d give 11 stars if I could for these GD breakfast tacos. OMFG. Head shakingly good

I wanted to give it 4.5 stars, but not possible, but 5 is closer to the truth than 4...  Excellent food. I am not a big fan of avocados, but their avocado salsa was amazing! I had the breakfast burrito and it was excellent, but I did have them hold the creamy cilantro sauce as I hate cilantro.  They had live entertainment the night we were there, and that was fun. The only downside was only one waitress. Service was not "slow", just not quite as attentive as I wanted. A pitcher of water left at the table would have solved my picky problem. We will definitely go back!
no freezer, no microwave, they make it all from scratch. Really tasty

Maria, the owner of The high  Note just served us one of the best breakfast I’ve ever eaten, vegan or not.  I felt like we were eating at her home.  The atmosphere, the music and the conversation was a joy!  I will be back and you should Join me, if you are not vegan you may come to scoff, but come back after you realize how great Maria’s food is.  Bon appétit

The waitress was very friendly and helpful! The place was cozy and accommodated to us bringing our toddler along. Unfortunately I did not like any of the food, and my husband wasn’t a big fan either (although he said he “didn’t mind” the burrito too much). We got the breakfast burrito and grilled cheese, and hummus and chips. It was all very oily and the grilled cheese especially was very bland, on top of the “cheese” not being melted. We have had our fair share of vegan food, so it’s not that we had “Omni expectations” or anything, but the quality for the price definitely will not have us returning especially as we didn’t even finish our meal.

Vegan only restaurant. Small space that is well designed and comfortable, ambiance is on point.  Food was delicious! Drinks were superb. Friendly staff.  We went on a Saturday and there was only one server for all of the tables. If the restaurant had a flat top, not griddles, to cook the food with, I could see the process speeding up. It’s worth the wait, but we were there 2.5 hours, an hour longer than a typical restaurant.

Super amazing vegan food left me very surprised. The only downside is long wait times as they cook on residential griddles and only have 1 waitress.  That said, everyone was incredibly kind and the food and atmosphere was fantastic. I really enjoyed my burrito.

What a great experience. 💯 vegan menu in the cutest little cafe. Each dish we tried had great flavors. Casual experience. It’s a great little breakfast/lunch cafe translated into a vegan menu experience without compromising the flavors and heart feel of a cafe/diner. We loved it.
Amazing! Great food, great service, great management!!
Really tasty food and cocktails, friendly service staff who were very overwhelmed by the volume of customers. Would rate five stars in a heartbeat if they had adequate staffing.
AWESOME place for local music and fun place for tacos and meetting ladies
Amazing breakfast sandwich and torta!

Loved the food at this restaurant and their casual ambience. I have tried their breakfast menu during a workday and their brunch menu during the weekend. Loved their bruschetta sandwich with lentil soup, pesto sandwich with coconut tomato soup, high note potatoes and high note scramble (tofu) for their natural, fresh flavors brought out by delicate cooking with few spices/condiments. Very friendly staff!  There is no doubt that this is “the best restaurant for vegans and vegetarians”!
Wish I could go here more often if I lived closer, incredible vegan food so happy to have this place in the treasure valley. The breakfast burrito was so good.

Read the reviews and, as a vegan, I was excited to try High Note Cafe with my family. When we stepped inside, it was dark, dingy, humid, and smelled strongly of patchouli. The cafe is very small and cramped. It was uncomfortable already but we decided to try it anyways.  There were multiple tables that needed to be cleared off so we were greeted by a waitress and told that she would have someone clean off a table for us. We waited for about 5 minutes for a table to be cleaned off. We sat ourselves down and waited for menus. Again, 7 minutes went by and the waitress finally came over to offer us menus.  Because the service was so slow, I had plenty of time to observe the room. Most tables had food and, to the Cafe’s credit, it looked appetizing. Staff seemed to do a lot of standing around, which was confusing based on how long we were waiting for everything. The music was loud enough that it wasn’t easy to have a conversation. We had to shout at one another as we discussed whether we should stay or leave because (at that point) we had already been there 20 minutes and had not been approached for an order of any kind.  Ultimately, we decided to leave because the service was so bad, it wasn’t worth trying the food to deal with the service and the uncomfortable atmosphere (as stated above, it was stuffy, humid, and did not seem particularly clean). When I found the waitress to tell her that we were going to leave, she said, “Yeah. Sorry about that.”  I have never written a review but I felt compelled to share my experience with others. As a vegan, I was so excited to try High Note Cafe so I was beyond disappointed. We do not live in the area and made a special trip just for this restaurant. i am not one to walk out of a restaurant but it was the worst dining experience myself and my family has ever had.
The food was very tasty, our server Amy was excellent. I love the vibe, I can't wait to go when they have live music.
I love this place!!!! Amazing breakfast burritos!!

Nice plant-based cafe. Wonderful tomato basil soup and the ceasar salad was really good. Way too much salt in the lentil soup and a whole grain bread option would be nice. Overall we'll go again and recommend to friends.
Awesome vegan food. Makes me feel very comfortable being a vegan and all. Live music in the weekends too
It's nice going into a place knowing everything is vegan! Also hosts some really cool shows at night.
This place is meat eater approved. The brunch menu was very good and filling!
Great place! Food is great, amazing atmosphere, and very friendly staff. Breakfast burrito was very good.

Amazing service, fresh tasty food, great location, fabulous music. What more can you ask for? Visiting from Denver, I can wholeheartedly say this place contends with any vegan eatery in the Denver/boulder area. Will visit again next time I’m in Boise👍🏻👍🏻

Fantastic! We are new to the plant-based diet and thought we'd give this a try. Wonderful service, cozy atmosphere, and amazing food!! So glad there's a place we can go and pick anything from the menu.

This place is a godsend for those that are vegan in Boise. Good vegan food is my quest. Most restaurants have options that are mostly vegetarian or a very small choice of vegan options but this place is all vegan, all the time. In fact it’s the best food experience I’ve had in Boise in my two years of living here because they had tons of choices for me. This place is stellar For vegans and I am now one of their BIGGEST fans.
Delicious and queer-friendly!

As a life-long meat eater, I was skeptical of this place, but after having lunch today, my life has been changed! I had no idea vegan food could be so good. The African squash soup was some of the best soup I ever had and the gyro was so good! Very impressed.

I have no idea how this place is a 4.6 outta 5 stars... 5 stars all across the board from me. Absolutely amazing vegan food. Taco Tuesday has 4 variations of vegan street tacos and they are all amazingly tasty. We're not even from boise but if we ever come thru we'll be stopping here!!!

I'm so happy that we have an exclusively vegan place in town! Their breakfast burrito is amazing!! They have really been working on improving their customer service recently and it is much appreciated!
Love this place! It's become our Sunday tradition to get breakfast here
Staff was great and the food was incredible. Can’t wait to go back!
Great service. Fantastic breakfast burrito. Chili could use some work, but was a solid *okay*
They get their ingredients from the co-op which is nice. The pesto mushroom tomato sandwich was incredibly flavorful. Will come back for taco Tuesday for sure.
I strayed from my original plan of trying a sandwich and got the $1.50 street tacos. They were good but I'm definitely coming back for a sandwhich.
Very rude staff, bad advertising, racist to my friend, not a good place zero stars of I could
Friendly staff and great food. Nice Friday night vibe!
Go here. Do it. Food is amazing, generous serving sizes, we always leave satisfied. Our favorite restaurant in Boise!!

OMG!! First time eating there today.  The food was exceptional! My tastebuds were singing with joy! I had the street tacos and they were fantastic! My congrats to the Chef and owner for an outstanding meal! I will return!
I had the vegan gyro from here, it was spot on spectacular
Food and menu is over rated! Very inflexible and not very good service!
Great food! Especially breakfast dishes!
Amazing
Listen to poetry, read your own, brave karaoke or just enjoy a decent bowl of tomato soup and a seitan sandwich with homemade bread.
I am not vegan, but was absolutely shocked by the taste of this food. Vegan mozzarella was fantastic.
The move to an all vegan menu is greatly appreciated! Great product, great service!

I’ve been coming here for years and it never disappoints. The owner is the sweetest and I love the care that goes into making sure the food is fresh, healthy and consistent. The vegan tomato basil is my favorite in town and the house made bread for the sandwiches is amazing. I highly recommend the vegan torta sandwich. The recent switch to an all vegan menu seems to be have done effortlessly and I appreciate this as the options in Boise for vegans are pretty limited. 5/5 highly recommend!

High Note Cafe is definitely worth a visit. The food is tremendous, the music is great, and the staff are very friendly. I honestly couldn't recommend this restaurant highly enough and they have my overwhelming support.

Amazing. Get the grilled cheese w/ tomato soup. It's the best meal I've ever eaten.  EDIT: For those who don't know, the High Note has adopted a fully-vegan menu. Good for them, but it's a real shame for me. Their grilled cheese was the best in the world, and the impression-cheese just doesn't live up to the original. I'm only dropping one star, because A) going vegan is a morally positive thing to do, so good on them, B) the tomato soup is still godlike, and C) it served as a great meeting place for my uncle and I for years. It was great for so long, I can't bear to drop more than one star. It's just a shame that I'll never be able to have that incredible grilled cheese sandwich anymore. If it ever comes back, I'll come back, but until then it's an unfortunate farewell from me.
Delicious food and a wonderful staff that are doing their best to serve ethical sustainable meals.
Great food and friendly staff.  Had a wonderful morning on the patio eating and reading the paper while visiting Boise.

I've been going to vegan establishments with my dad for 30 years, this one is solid. The scrambled tofu was fantastic. There was a waitress with I think a bird tattoo on her arm. She was really nice. Good times.
Cool spot for vegan grub and DIY shows

I have been wanting to try this place for a long time. So refreshing to order off a menu and not have to ask what is in everything. Service was great! Atmosphere was cozy and the food is amazing. I will definitely be back!!!
Great place for a vegan brunch on Saturday. Torta is highly recommend.
Wow, Boise has a great vegan place. Black bean tacos for lunch and I feel like a million bucks.
Great restaurant with vegan faire
This is probably one of the BEST resteraunts you will EVER go to! AMAZING food and FANTASTIC service!!!

Good location, but the service is a bit slow. Give 15-20 minutes from order to food, any time of day this is how long it takes. Everything is cooked fresh though. They recently converted to full vegan on everything if that’s your thing. I had the tofu scrambler and it was good.  Probably won’t come back, since I’m generally opposed to vegan food, but that’s no reflection on the restaurant.

I'm not vegan but my oh my was it delicious, we took our vegan friends and they were impressed. A do over for sure! We had the torta and breakfast burrito and pancakes. Delicious! Service was great and friendly!
Epic and service!!

100% Vegan. 100% Awesome.  “No freezers, no microwaves, home-made everything,” and you can tell. Every time I come here, the food is very delicious. This time around I had the Rosemary Seitan Sandwich and the Creamy Mushroom and Vegetable Soup. And omg, the soup was the best creamy mushroom I’ve had in my life. The wait wasn’t long at all and the service was delightful. This is my favorite spot to eat when I come to Boise!
Would rate higher if I could. Their vegan grilled cheese is excellent!
Delicious brunch & a local business very deserving of your support

This place is so amazing. The only all vegan restaurant in Boise that I know of!! Great atmosphere and the food is so good. Kid friendly too since they have vegan grilled cheese! I highly recommend supporting this locally owned vegan restaurant.
The food was amazing and the service was awesome!
Perfect cafe <3
Vegan!
After sitting down it took an 1hr 15 min to get our food. Ridiculously slow. They were out of several things. The food was good and i’d come back if it didn’t take forever to get the food.

Their service is such a huge disappointment we ended up leaving without even eating. When we arrived we stood in the entry for a few minutes, none of the multiple employees standing/eating behind the counter greeted us they just kept looking at us. We weren't  sure what to do so we thought maybe we need to seat ourselves since no one was saying anything, at the time we didn't notice the broken "please wait to be seated" sign stuffed in a highchair by the door. When we tried to seat ourselves a waitress snapped at us telling us we need to wait for her to seat us. So we went back to the door and waited a few more minutes. The waitress finally asked us how many were in our party but then went outside and started helping another table. At that point we decided to leave and apparently the waitress thought it was funny because she laughed as we walked past her. I'd been looking forward to trying this place for weeks and want to support vegan restaurants, but unfortunately we won't be returning do to their lack of service.
Love this place for brunch. I'm not vegan but the vegan breakfast tacos are delicious.
Vegan? Lol, I really do hope it stays open. Otherwise that's less jobs for people.

Thank you to offer an amazing and delicious array of plant based options ... Vegan cuisine is the Future... your cafe represents compassion and health and yumminess 😊 gladly will come back and support again!
Amazing food, so happy to have a vegan place to eat at!! I went there for the first time and was quite pleased with their pesto sandwich.
My friend and I fell in love with this cafe. Lol Vegan comfort food!
Thank you for choosing compassion and logic and making your business, vegan!  💜
Thank you for going vegan!
High Note - High Five
Great vibe, friend staff and fabulous (plant based) food, what more can you ask for?!

Pictured is the vegan breakfast burrito and DANG it did not disappoint. It was one of those meals I didn't stop thinking about after we left. I usually think vegan meals that use tofu are a cop-out but everything was so well seasoned, so many yummy ingredients, and it was huge!! Unique decor and music, a hole-in-the-wall gem of a place.  Note that since it's a small restaurant with fresh ingredients, they may run out of certain things (I believe we were the last table of the day to be able to get avocado with our dishes and we were there at about noon, which was 3 hours before closing).  Only complaint is that it was severely understaffed, hoping that someone called in sick and that's not a regular occurrence as it took about 30 min to order food (they had one waitress running their entire floor, but honestly she rocked it). Regardless of the wait, the food was amazing and we will be back for sure.
2$ mimosas and avocadoes, what more could you want?

This place has the worst service in Boise. I came here for a post mates delivery and was rudely greeted...Then no one took my order for 10 minutes. (When my order was finally taken, it was by a cook, not the waitress). The live music was way too loud and the singer was not good. Then, the food took almost 30 minutes to be made. For grilled cheese and premade soup...They adressed me as "postmates lady" instead of coming up and saying "excuse me". And when i went to pay they rudely adressed the total. No smile, no "thank you for coming" nothing. Never eating here myself. Going to Guidos next door.
Very friendly service. Fancy food.  Wonderful experience.
Excellent service, delicious food, and a very nice vibe!
The Tomato soup the best I've ever had.. The waitress was very nice and service was great.. Will be back again..
Great food with a fun atmosphere. Many different flavors of mimosas and drinks that are great.
Great food and great music
Delicious, fresh tasting food with wonderful friendly service :) I'll definitely go again!
Amazing food

A special little gem tucked away in downtown boise. Cant get enough!!! Great food and a surprisingly vast menu for being a small cafe. Everything made in house and from scratch with vegan options. Even items get sourced from local growers. It's a great environment. There always seems to be something going on. I've caught local music, traveling bands, karaoke, and more. Ever since discovering about a year ago, I cant stay away. Always something yummy to eat. Plus handmade juices. Fresh juice lemonades are the best in the summer. It's a place where you can take your time and slow down to enjoy the atmosphere or friends. Definitely worth checking out.
Chowder was a bit thin, but hi the spot.  Good live music.

Went here for first Thursday they have really delicious mimosas but it kind of seems like it was the food you could make it home so we didn't bother buying any.  But they had funny stuff in the bathroom that people had wrote on the walls so that was entertaining as well! It was so incredibly hot in there though.
This place serves some legitimate homemade food no matter what you order make sure you get toast with it they make homemade bread and it's delicious
Great food, wish we had more awesome places like this in Boise.

So GOOD. This place is Boise's hidden gem that everyone has passed but no one has actually entered. EVERYTHING is made from scratch, including the bread! There is a bit of a wait for food, but the wait is so very worth it. Have not had a single thing that wasn't absolutely stellar.
Great brunch!
Excellent food! Excellent service. Highly recommended!

This is a fun place..the menu seems boring..nothing super exciting..but it's good food..and the breakfast tacos were amazing..what will bring me back..it the mimosas!!.they are far from boring and they change them up .blueberry basil..cucumber raspberry..raspberry mint..strawberry cilantro..those are just a few..you will leave there happy you went for sure!!!!
The food was amazing with many options.  I had the breakfast tacos and I loved them and I had enough to share. I will definitely return!
Hip, happening, and awesome

I never write reviews but this place 100% deserves one. First off, the food is AMAZING! Everything is made from scratch and you can tell there are no shortcuts made. I have had several items but my favorite are the breakfast burrito with avocado(served all day) grilled cheese and tomato soup (a classic done right) and the Ruben is the best I’ve ever had. The atmosphere is great, they have good live music occasionally and waitstaff is always friendly. On Sunday’s they have a great deal on mimosas, not cheapy mimosas either I’m talking like blueberry basil mimosas with house made juices, I literally cannot say enough good things about this place. Great job!
My soup and sandwich were both fresh and delicious. The interior needs some brightening up but the food is worth the visit!

The high note cafe is a very special place. I have been regularly eating here since they first opened a few years ago. High Note has wonderful food. WONDERFUL FOOD! The club sandwich is my current favorite, but I've gone through phases where I woke up craving the Torta and I spent months where I only wanted to eat their reuben. The street Tacos are better than the taco destinations nearby by miles, and the seasonal soups always surprise me with how damn good they are. Beyond the food though, is the magic. If you're from Boise, you know we have had some classic spots over the years. We still have a couple, but we've lost places like the Brick Oven Bistro (Beanery). High Note has the feel of a classic Boise spot. The owner, Maria, is often serving food, and her eyes literally sparkle when she sees someone enjoying their food. High Note supports local artists, musicians, and poets strongly, and has relied on word of mouth for their success. This is a low key punk rock diner tucked away on a quieter corner of downtown Boise, and it is my favorite place to find myself on any given day. There is only one High Note, and if you aren't regularly there, you are literally missing out on the best eating experience in Boise. If I had to pick one meal to try out, I would suggest the club or the Torta with whatever the seasonal soup is and a glass of their iced tea.
Fresh and organic! Love it!
Awesome little spot for fare and drinks, staff is very friendly
Poetry
Consistently excellent food and service, I cannot recommended this place highly enough.
Great environment, excellent food.
Stopped in after a bike ride. Delicious homemade soup and bread. Outdoor patio space is great for people watching.
Just yum!

A hidden gem in Old Boise! Highly recommended for breakfast, lunch. dinner, pie & coffee, or drinks! Occasional karaoke and live music to spice things up! Can't get enough of their breakfast burrito or breakfast potatoes, veggie sandwich and homemade soups. OH AND THE PIES! Oh my god the pies...

Happy Hour-- Monday - Friday 4-6 PM. $1 off local beer, wine by the glass and special mimosas! Select $5 appetizers: Bruschetta or Hummus served with HIgh Note Toast or Chips & Dip-- Happy Hour could use some work, IMO.  Wow, what a great place! I've had it on my bookmarks now for well over a year. Not sure why I hadn't visited here before. I'm downtown a lot, but since it's tucked on a side street, I've just not noticed it.  Walking in it isn't much-- just a small room, bright yet old colors on the wall, local artwork, hippy vibe, with a bar area, small amount of seating, and a relaxed albeit modern feel to it.  $1 mimosas (first two) on Sundays. They have four flavors. We had the pineapple and cucumber.  Everything here is fresh! They don't have microwaves, and even hand wash the dishes.  We had some super good food! We shared a Caesar salad (average... it's lettuce!) and breakfast avocado taco-- AMAZING! A++  Here you can get homemade dessert, too. They oftentimes have live music, poets club, and $1 Taco Tuesdays!  All-in-all, the food was good, the service was good, chill/relaxed environment, and a good weekend brunch menu (select items on Sunday only). I recommed you try it!  BTW-- it is located next to Guidos New York Style Pizza behind Flying M Coffee in Downtown Boise.

Super delicious place to get a bite to eat. Best dollar taco Tuesdays in town, at least from what I have experienced, being vegetarian. The owner is very kind and good-hearted. Local business. Great beer selection. The customer service is fantastic and unique and I will be sure to continue coming here for a long time!
So much fun we did karaoke. It was so much fun! Played sweet Caroline. Me thinks everyone liked it
Love the atmosphere, very organic and warm
Great fresh food, lots of selection, friendly staff and owner, awesome pie.

The atmosphere is cozy. They had local musicians which play well and with heart. Had their salad and chips with beans which were good. Enjoyed that tap IPA Beers. Have been there twice and will go back for their poetry reading. Staff seemed pleasant.
Too many flies in here to eat the food.
The owners and staff are very friendly and helpful.   This is our favorite brunch place, and the Pico scramble and variety of mimosas are excellent.

Ehhh....I tried this place for a quick lunch:  - lots of choices on the menu - pretty easy to get to - service was average - much of the menu is overpriced - it was a battle with the numerous flies over who got to try our entrees first, we were inside too.  My wife's dish was good, but my sandwich was only OK.  The bread and butter combo they used was a bit odd and the meat light on taste.  I may return when it's cooler for another meal with the family.  The large menu means there's lot to pick from.

I really like the way the cafe is set up, the artwork and food are amazing. But the service has been so bad the past few times we have gone. This place was very abstract and fun to be in however the food is poorly lacking. The coleslaw was very vinegary and wouldn't recommend it also the pork Ruben sandwich was not good. We split one sandwich and paid almost $20 No thank-you.

Known about this place for a few years and finally gave it a shot. My only regret is that I didn't try it sooner. Food was incredibly fresh and tasted amazing. For a soup/breakfast/sandwich joint the attention to detail was incredible. Great local beer selection and good prices. Servers were friendly and helpful and the food came out quickly. Will be back for sure!!

My band Roobber's Roost played a show in this little coffee shop and it was OFF THE WALL. People are so amazing here! The owner of the place is incredibly sweet and hospitable! It's a must stop coffee shop! Tip them!!!

I love it here. All the food is made from scratch every morning, never using any microwaves, and it tastes amazing. Taco Tuesdays is a killer deal. And their soups will blow your mind. I come here weekly.

In this tiny place, everything is house made, even the toast on the side of their soups (mmmm), and the kraut on some sandwiches. Taco Tuesday is not to be missed ($1 street tacos). Pies, when they have them, are phenomenal Live music randomly. A friendly, relaxed place at night, I'm told that it has quite a lunch rush.
